# 14. Assessment Execution Framework

Following successful completion of planning, scope definition, and authorization activities defined in Part 1, the assessment shall transition into the operational execution phase.

The execution phase shall follow a structured, evidence-driven workflow designed to ensure consistency, repeatability, and technical accuracy across all assessment engagements.

Every assessment activity shall be:

* Scope-driven
* Evidence-based
* Risk-focused
* Vendor-neutral
* Fully traceable
* Technically validated
* Documented in accordance with EFSAF-STD-001

The Lead Assessor shall maintain overall responsibility for coordinating assessment activities, managing quality checkpoints, and ensuring adherence to the approved methodology.

