# 23. Threat Prevention Review Methodology

Threat prevention capabilities provide proactive protection beyond traditional packet filtering.

The assessment shall evaluate all deployed prevention technologies.

---

## 23.1 Assessment Scope

Depending on deployment, the review may include:

* Intrusion Prevention System (IPS)
* Intrusion Detection System (IDS)
* Anti-malware
* Antivirus
* Anti-spyware
* Anti-bot
* Web filtering
* DNS security
* URL filtering
* Application control
* File inspection
* Sandbox integration
* SSL/TLS inspection
* Email security integration
* Threat intelligence feeds
* Reputation services
