# 37. Recommendation Development Methodology

Recommendations shall enable practical improvement of the firewall security posture.

Each recommendation shall:

* Address the identified root cause
* Reduce business risk
* Be technically feasible
* Be prioritized
* Consider operational impact
* Be measurable
* Support long-term improvement

Recommendations should avoid unnecessary product-specific guidance unless required by the assessment scope.

---

## 37.1 Recommendation Categories

Recommendations may be categorized as:

* Immediate Remediation
* Short-Term Improvement
* Medium-Term Enhancement
* Strategic Initiative
* Governance Improvement
* Operational Improvement
* Architecture Improvement
* Monitoring Enhancement
* Documentation Improvement
* Training Requirement

---

# 38. Exception Management

Assessment exceptions shall be formally documented.

Exception categories include:

* Scope limitations
* Technical constraints
* Environmental restrictions
* Unsupported technologies
* Approved deviations
* Operational dependencies
* Third-party ownership

Every exception shall include:

* Description
* Business justification
* Impact assessment
* Risk implications
* Approval authority
* Review date

---

# 39. Assessment Decision Framework

The assessment methodology shall use standardized decision outcomes for every evaluated control.

| Decision                   | Definition                                                  |
| -------------------------- | ----------------------------------------------------------- |
| Compliant                  | Control fully satisfies assessment criteria                 |
| Compliant with Observation | Control is effective but minor improvements are recommended |
| Partially Compliant        | Control exists but does not fully satisfy requirements      |
| Non-Compliant              | Control fails to satisfy assessment requirements            |
| Not Applicable             | Control is outside the approved assessment scope            |
| Unable to Validate         | Insufficient evidence to determine compliance               |

Assessors shall document the rationale for every decision.

---

# 40. Quality Control Checkpoints

Before reporting, the Lead Assessor shall verify that:

* All assessment controls have been evaluated.
* Findings are supported by evidence.
* Risk ratings follow EFSAF-RISK-001.
* Compliance mappings follow EFSAF-MAP-001.
* Scores align with EFSAF-SCORE-001.
* Recommendations address identified root causes.
* Documentation complies with EFSAF-STD-001.
* Evidence references are complete and traceable.
* No unsupported conclusions remain.

Any deficiencies identified during quality control shall be corrected before proceeding to the reporting phase.

