# 41. Report Development Methodology

The assessment report is the primary deliverable of every EFSAF engagement and shall provide an accurate, evidence-based representation of the organization's firewall security posture.

Report development shall begin only after:

* All assessment activities have been completed.
* Evidence has been validated.
* Findings have undergone technical review.
* Risk ratings have been finalized.
* Compliance mappings have been verified.
* Security scoring has been completed.
* Quality assurance checkpoints have been satisfied.

All reports shall conform to **EFSAF-TMP-001** and **EFSAF-REP-001**.

---

